 Bishop Bridget Okafoagu of the New Convenient of God Mission will finally be laid to mother earth on Friday, June 17, 2022. According to statement signed by Arch Bishop Emma David Okafoagu (Husband of the deceased), with gratitude to God and total submission to the will of almighty, the family of Arch Bishop (Prof) Emma David Okoroafo of Obiagu, Uruagu, Nnewi in Nnewi South Local Government Area of Anambra State and the entire membership of New Covenant of God Mission wishes to announce the transition to the great beyond of our beloved Bishop, wife, mother, sister, grandmother BishopBridget Eagle Nwakalfe Okafoagu. The funeral will kickstart with a Service of songs at New Covenant of God Mission, Nnewi on Thursday 16 June at 4pm while the funeral service will take place on Friday 17 at 7am the body leaves Nnamdi Azikiwe Teaching Hospital Morgue, Nnewi to New Covenant of God Mission, Nnewi at Uruagu Village along Oba Okigwe Road in Nnewi. However, there will be an outing service at the same New Covenant of God Mission, Nnewi on Sunday 19 June by 9am. Also, a statement made available by the Prof Solomon Uzochukwu Susu, the Proprietor Susu College, disclosed that thememories shared with Bishop Bridget Nwakalfe Okafoagu will never be forgotten, adding that her kindness will be greatly missed. According to Susu, “she had the heart that cared completely. She had the smile that brought so much pleasure. She had the love that brought joy beyond measure. “We have lost a gem, a wonderful servant of God, always there for all. May God almighty grant Arch Bishop (Prof) Emma David Okoroafo and the entire family the strength to bear the irreparable loss.”